=1> Cabilis was not a forgiving home to be born into.  A city of Cazic-Thule's followers is not given to the gentler style of upbringing, so other Iksar ranked almost as high as the occasional escaped slave on the list of terrors for young Chmee.  From the God of his people he learned that fear is power and from observing his own people as he grew he saw that strength, perceived or real, could create fear.<br>
<br>
Chmee knew little of his family and cared still less, for there is no family unit among the beings that swim the dark canals of the Iksar city.  With the others of his brood he swam into the canals after being hatched, there to feed and grow strong - or die and vanish unmourned.  In his early days, beyond his remembering now, he saw the older tads consume new broodlings and in his turn consume his younger kin as he grew, until he was past that stage of development and began to spend more time walking than swimming.<br>
<br>
Along with many other young Iksar he went to the place of testing, to determine what his path in life would be.  The necromancers had gained ascendancy in the cruel politics of the city at this time and so it was they were given first pick of this new generation.  Chmee showed no aptitude for their dark magic and so was passed on to the other guilds.<br>
<br>
Other tests came and went.  Not devout enough to become a shaman, too uncomfortable around magic even to become a shadow knight (for indeed magic seemed, somehow, deeply wrong to him) and finding the heavy armour of the warriors too awkward he went on for testing by the less glamorous professions.  One by one, all turned him down, for they saw in him a spirit that could not be tamed and that would not settle for being a lesser denizen of this place.<br>
<br>
Disconsolate and ashamed, yet still defiant, Chmee walked from the testing hall, muttering curses under his breath against the guildmasters he considered fools.  A figure moved out from the shadows and addressed him as he stalked by.<br>
<br>
&quot;So, you think yourself better than those placed above you?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I think their so called professions are a sham!  They fail to utilise our greatest gifts.  I may know nothing of the world, but I know what we are.  To rely on our God as the shamans do is folly, for who would trust his life to a god of fear?  Equally magic seems able to fail and such failure could too easily end your life.  Then our warriors, who encumber themselves with armour when we are already armoured...and they move so slowly!  There must be something more than this.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;There is, but they are not to be found at the Halls of Testing.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Who then?  Why would they not do as all others do and find those who are suitable for their path?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;The Swift Tails, those who follow the way of the claw.  We do not need to test all those who go to the halls and indeed we have more important things to do with our time.  Those who are able to join us will not be able to follow any other - as you were not.  This is part of your first lesson, if you can become one of us.  Know yourself and what you are.&quot;<br>
<br>
Without speaking another word the strange Iksar turned and walked along the bank of one of the many canals.  With questions filling his mind, but none passing his lips, Chmee followed and sealed his fate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub37.ezboard.com/unanookt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nanook T</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ph3aR my witty sig</span><br>  Posts: 181<br> <font color=#70DB93>(1/30/02 4:34:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub37.ezboard.com/flexinvictusfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=78.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Beginnings</span><hr size=1> Very good!  Excellent background!  More please! <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub37.ezboard.com/flexinvictusfrm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=78.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub37.ezboard.com/flexinvictusfrm2.showNextMessage?topicID=78.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub37.ezboard.com/flexinvictusfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=78.topic&index=1><img src=http://synnovea.no-frills.net/ezboard/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub37.ezboard.com/flexinvictusfrm2.threadControl?topicID=78.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub37.ezboard.com/flexinvictusfrm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=78.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub37.ezboard.com/flexinvictusfrm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=78.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notificat